    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Are you using Hibernate's <code>Query</code> object, or JPA? For JPA, it should work fine:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String jpql = \"from A where name in (:names)\";\nQuery q = em.createQuery(jpql);\nq.setParameter(\"names\", l);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For Hibernate's, you'll need to use the setParameterList:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String hql = \"from A where name in (:names)\";\nQuery q = s.createQuery(hql);\nq.setParameterList(\"names\", l);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1988337,
      "reputation" : 622,
      "user_id" : 1782997,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96de043638333fdcbcd24c9015edca0c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Attila T",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1782997/attila-t"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1454081368,
    "creation_date" : 1454081368,
    "answer_id" : 35088132,
    "question_id" : 4828049,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using pure JPA with <em>Hibernate 5.0.2.Final</em> as the actual provider the following seems to work with positional parameters as well:</p>\n\n<p>Entity.java:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Entity\n@NamedQueries({\n    @NamedQuery(name = \"byAttributes\", query = \"select e from Entity e where e.attribute in (?1)\") })\npublic class Entity {\n    @Column(name = \"attribute\")\n    private String attribute;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Dao.java:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Dao {\n    public List&lt;Entity&gt; findByAttributes(Set&lt;String&gt; attributes) {\n        Query query = em.createNamedQuery(\"byAttributes\");\n        query.setParameter(1, attributes);\n\n        List&lt;Entity&gt; entities = query.getResultList();\n        return entities;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6593416,
      "reputation" : 29545,
      "user_id" : 5093961,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3736a281ed5cdc18e41f6d3100d76dcc?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Steven Spungin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5093961/steven-spungin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1472407696,
    "creation_date" : 1472407696,
    "answer_id" : 39194317,
    "question_id" : 4828049,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Leaving out the parenthesis and simply calling 'setParameter' now works with at least Hibernate.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String jpql = \"from A where name in :names\";\nQuery q = em.createQuery(jpql);\nq.setParameter(\"names\", l);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
